---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Accessibility | One Less Thing"
  description="One Less Thing is committed to WCAG 2.2 AA accessibility. Learn about our standards, known issues, and how to reach us if something isn't working."
>

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h1>Accessibility statement</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        We build this site for everyone — including disabled people who depend on
        accessible technology every day. Here's what we've done, what we're working on,
        and how to tell us when something isn't working.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container--narrow page-body">

    <section aria-labelledby="commitment-heading">
      <h2 id="commitment-heading">Our commitment</h2>
      <p>
        One Less Thing is committed to meeting the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2,
        Level AA. These guidelines define how to make web content accessible to people with
        disabilities — including visual, auditory, motor, cognitive, and speech disabilities.
      </p>
      <p>
        Accessibility is not a feature we bolt on at the end. It's a baseline requirement
        for every page we publish. A financial literacy resource that isn't accessible to
        disabled people has failed its core audience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="measures-heading">
      <h2 id="measures-heading">What we've done</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Structured all pages with proper heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3) so screen readers can navigate by heading.</li>
        <li>Added a skip-to-main-content link at the top of every page so keyboard users can bypass navigation.</li>
        <li>Written descriptive alt text for all meaningful images. Decorative images are marked with empty alt attributes.</li>
        <li>Maintained color contrast ratios that meet or exceed WCAG 2.2 AA (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text).</li>
        <li>Ensured all interactive elements are keyboard-navigable and have visible focus indicators.</li>
        <li>Used semantic HTML elements (<code>nav</code>, <code>main</code>, <code>article</code>, <code>section</code>) rather than generic divs wherever structure matters.</li>
        <li>Set the page language (<code>lang="en"</code>) on every page so screen readers use the correct pronunciation.</li>
        <li>Tested layouts on a range of viewport sizes so content is readable without horizontal scrolling at 320px width.</li>
        <li>Avoided content that flashes more than 3 times per second.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="known-heading">
      <h2 id="known-heading">Known limitations</h2>
      <p>
        We are a small team, and we may not have caught everything. Issues we are aware of:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Newsletter embed:</strong> The Beehiiv signup form on the Newsletter page
          is a third-party embed. We do not control its accessibility. If the embed does not
          work for you, please <a href="/newsletter">email us directly</a> and we will add
          you to the list manually.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If you encounter a barrier we haven't listed here, please tell us — we want to fix it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <h2 id="contact-heading">Contact us</h2>
      <p>
        If you experience an accessibility barrier on this site, we want to know.
        Please reach out at <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a>
        with a description of the issue and the page where you found it.
        We will respond within 2 business days.
      </p>
      <p>
        If we are unable to resolve your issue, we can help you find the information
        you need in an alternative format.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="standards-heading">
      <h2 id="standards-heading">Technical standards</h2>
      <p>
        This site conforms to WCAG 2.2 Level AA. Content is built using HTML5 and Astro.
        We test with keyboard-only navigation and use automated tools to check for common issues.
        We do not use any overlays or third-party accessibility plugins — these are not
        a substitute for building accessibly from the start.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="updated-heading">
      <h2 id="updated-heading">Statement date</h2>
      <p>This accessibility statement was last reviewed on May 6, 2026.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="disclaimer" role="note">
      <p>
        <em>This content is for educational purposes only and does not constitute legal, tax,
        or financial advice. Consult a qualified professional for your specific situation.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .page-header h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-body); }
  .page-body { padding: 3rem 1.5rem; }
  .page-body section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-body h2 { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-body ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .page-body li { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .page-body p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  code {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    font-size: 0.875em;
  }
  .disclaimer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }
  .disclaimer p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
</style>
